posts.title: That man from NY
posts.content:
In 1986 a farmer took his own life on the morning his farm was to go to a courthouse auction, believing his life insurance would pay enough to save the cotton & soybean plantation that has been in his family for over 100 years. A complete stranger in New York read about this story & paid off the remaining $77,000.

A USMC Sergeant was beaten and tortured for 7 months in a Mexican prison for accidentally crossing the border with a firearm. Once released, the NY man sent him $25,000 “To get you started.”

In 2013 A black bus driver saved a suicidal girl from jumping off a bridge. Our NY man sent him $10,000.

A Rabbi’s critically ill son needed to go from NYC to California for treatment in 1988. No airline would fly him. NY man paid for a private flight for the child.

In 2017 after Army Corporal Dillon Baldridge was killed in Afghanistan, NY man sent his father $25,000.

This kind-hearted man from Queens has committed many other “quiet acts of random kindness.”

Ed McMahon was dying of cancer, the bank was foreclosing on his house, and put him on the street. NY man bought the house and let him live there.

A wise man once said, “If a man’s heart is good, nothing else matters, & if a man’s heart is bad, nothing else matters.” Who is this kind man? Donald J. Trump, a man with a good heart. Who, by the way, did not take a paycheck for being President.
